# Frontend Development Rules

## Typography
- **Primary Font**: IBM Plex Sans for all UI text
- **Monospace Font**: IBM Plex Mono for code/technical content
- **NEVER use**: Inter, Roboto, Arial, Geist, or generic sans-serif

## Type Scale
```
text-xs    → 12px  — Labels, captions, metadata
text-sm    → 14px  — Body text, form inputs, buttons
text-base  → 16px  — Primary body, paragraphs
text-lg    → 18px  — Section headers
text-xl    → 20px  — Page section titles
text-2xl   → 24px  — Page headers
text-3xl   → 30px  — Hero sections only
```

## Color Palette (Light Theme Only)
```css
gray-50:  '#fafafa'  /* Page background */
gray-100: '#f4f4f5'  /* Card backgrounds, hover */
gray-200: '#e4e4e7'  /* Borders, dividers */
gray-300: '#d4d4d8'  /* Disabled states */
gray-400: '#a1a1aa'  /* Placeholder text */
gray-500: '#71717a'  /* Secondary text */
gray-600: '#52525b'  /* Body text */
gray-700: '#3f3f46'  /* Primary text */
gray-800: '#27272a'  /* Headings */
gray-900: '#18181b'  /* High contrast */
```

## Component Rules
- Buttons: `h-9` standard, `h-8` compact, `rounded-md`
- Cards: `border border-gray-200 bg-white`, `shadow-sm` max
- Inputs: `h-9 border-gray-200 focus:border-gray-400`

## FORBIDDEN Patterns (AI Slop)
1. Purple/violet gradients on white backgrounds
2. Multiple font families in one view
3. Excessive shadows (shadow-md, shadow-lg, shadow-xl)
4. Rounded-full buttons for primary actions
5. Emoji in UI (unless user content)
6. Colorful icons — stick to monochrome
7. Hero sections with stock gradients
8. Glowing effects or neon colors
